					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">He just got lucky that blank space at the end of a ROM is filled in with FF bytes, which happens to be an offscreen value for Y coordinates.
<br />
<br />Also, that is probably the worst way to read the controller.  Should read all 8 bits into one byte, then XOR that with FF, then store that into a variable.  Whenever you need to test bits, just use lda #some_button \ BIT joypad_variable.  Condition flag is not zero (NE) if a button is being held down.
<br />
<br />Here's example code (untested, just written off the top of my head) that reads all 8 bits off the joypad.  You use another variable to hold what the last joypad state was, so you can tell when buttons have changed from not pressed to pressed.
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">read_joypad:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda joypad_state<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta previous_joypad_state<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;;strobe the controller<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda&nbsp; &nbsp;#$01<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$4016<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda&nbsp; &nbsp;#$00<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$4016<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;ldx #8&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />joypad_loop:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda $4016<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;ror a<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;rol joypad_state<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;dex<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bne joypad_loop<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda joypad_state<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;eor #$FF<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta joypad_state<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;eor previous_joypad_state<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;and joypad_state<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta joypad_pressed<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;rts<br /></div></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Here come the fortune cookies!  Here come the fortune cookies!  They're wearing paper hats!</div>
